    <abstract>With regard to the name Seng’an Daoyi, Yang Hao 50-51 reads “monk An Daoyi”: „seng“ as a title, „An“ as the monk’s  family name, 
        and „Daoyi“ as his given name. To buttress this reading, he quotes examples from votive inscriptions in which persons with secular
        names carry titles like 僧, 和尚, or 禪師.</abstract>
